import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the trend in wheat production over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year
    data = data.groupby('year').mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.axhline(y=data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='--', label='Average Wheat Production')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average wheat production per year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wheat', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat production?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
